Crumley Roberts Law Firm Names Brian L. Kinsley, Practice Group Leader
by Debra Adam | December 1st, 2011

Greensboro, N.C. – December 1, 2011 – Crumley Roberts, LLP names Brian Kinsley to Practice Group Leader for Mass Tort and Product Liability. Crumley Roberts is a North Carolina-based law firm that provides legal counsel on personal injury, workers’ compensation and Social Security disability claims.

	“I am confident in Brian's leadership and his ability to ensure that we are positioned for long-term growth and success,” said President and CEO Chris Roberts.

	Mr. Kinsley will be located in Greensboro and will head up the firm’s Mass Tort group, providing legal counsel to clients on drug injury, medical device defects and product liability matters. He is a graduate of Northeastern University in Boston, Massachusetts and received his law degree from Suffolk University.  He is a member of the bar in North Carolina, Massachusetts, Maryland and District of Columbia. Prior to joining Crumley Roberts in 2009, he worked on national cases involving drug and product liability for breast implants, Fen-Phen, vaccines and other defective products.

	Kinsley added: “I am happy for this new opportunity and for the forward-thinking of this firm as it relates to the Mass Tort area.  I am looking forward to this new role.”

	Founded in 1989, Crumley Roberts, LLP, represents individuals with personal injury, workers' compensation and Social Security disability claims. The firm operates from 14 offices in North Carolina and South Carolina. To learn more about the firm, or its community relations activities, visit www.crumleyroberts.com or stay connected on Twitter, Facebook or LinkedIn.

	— end —

	 

For More Information: 

	Stern Dixon, Director of Marketing

